00:39:52.760 --> 00:39:58.450
My position when it comes to the death penalty
is primarily the human factor.

00:39:58.450 --> 00:40:01.180
And that is, we all make mistakes.

00:40:01.180 --> 00:40:03.360
We do it all the time.

00:40:03.360 --> 00:40:08.510
We can be feeding the baby with a bottle and
we take the nipple and it hits the baby's

00:40:08.510 --> 00:40:09.640
chin.

00:40:09.640 --> 00:40:10.790
Mistake.

00:40:10.790 --> 00:40:12.780
We can make a wrong turn.

00:40:12.780 --> 00:40:14.130
Mistake.

00:40:14.130 --> 00:40:16.310
One person can get it wrong.

00:40:16.310 --> 00:40:19.130
12 people can get it wrong.

00:40:19.130 --> 00:40:22.230
100 people can make an honest mistake.

00:40:22.230 --> 00:40:23.730
We see it in baseball games.

00:40:23.730 --> 00:40:26.250
The player slide into the second base.

00:40:26.250 --> 00:40:29.230
The umpire says "He's out."

00:40:29.230 --> 00:40:33.440
On first review, he really was safe.

00:40:33.440 --> 00:40:37.100
That man can come out the dugout, and go back
to second base.

00:40:37.100 --> 00:40:41.000
But you can't bring a man back from the graveyard.

00:40:41.000 --> 00:40:42.800
And that's it right there.

00:40:42.800 --> 00:40:45.180
You don't want that innocence factor there.

00:40:45.180 --> 00:40:48.620
That you know that we all susceptible to.

00:40:48.620 --> 00:40:50.900
No matter how much we might wanna deny it.

00:40:50.900 --> 00:40:52.840
It is so true.

00:40:52.840 --> 00:40:54.630
We make mistakes.

00:40:54.630 --> 00:40:57.090
And who wanna be a mistake?

00:40:57.090 --> 00:40:58.740
Thank you.

